The paper discusses the use of second-order methods in machine learning and data analysis applications, specifically in the context of convex optimization. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of GPUs to accelerate the algorithms, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of sub-sampling techniques, which could potentially place it in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of these methods in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) applications, which further supports the possibility of these sub-categories.
